---
description: Testing and code quality rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Testing philosophy:
- Write production-quality code with tests for critical behavior.
- Prefer deterministic unit tests for business logic (moderation, policy evaluation, pipeline steps).
- Add integration tests for APIs, repositories, pipelines, and workflows crossing boundaries.
- Mock external services: OpenAI, Whisper, S3, Pinecone, PostgreSQL (or use test containers), webhooks.

Testing expectations:
- Add tests for non-trivial service methods (video_service, moderation_service, stream_service).
- Add tests for auth and permission-sensitive flows (RBAC, API keys).
- Add tests for AI/agent logic at the orchestration level where feasible (graphs, chains).
- Cover validation, failure, and edge cases (no frames, low confidence, policy mismatch, escalation).
- Mock frame extraction, Whisper, and vision APIs in tests; keep tests isolated.
- Keep tests readable and isolated; do not depend on live external APIs in normal test flows.

Code quality:
- Use linting and formatting (ruff for Python, eslint for frontend); use types wherever the stack supports them.
- Keep functions focused; refactor repeated logic into shared utilities when justified.

Do not:
- Add major logic without at least basic tests.
- Create brittle tests tied to unstable implementation details.
- Depend on live OpenAI, Whisper, S3, or Pinecone in normal test runs.
